Ivy Investment Management Company to Adopt Selector Management Funds From EMG | Business Wire
























































Ivy Investment Management Company to Adopt Selector Management Funds 
      From EMG






June 02, 2014 07:59 AM Eastern Daylight Time



OVERLAND PARK, Kan.--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Ivy Investment Management Company (“Ivy”) announced that it has executed 
      a fund adoption transaction agreement with Emerging Managers Group 
      (“EMG”) through which Ivy will take over responsibility as investment 
      adviser and distributor of the Selector Management Fund SICAV, an 
      umbrella UCITS fund range domiciled in Luxembourg.
    


      Following the closing of the fund adoption, expected on or around June 
      30, 2014, the UCITS funds will be distributed internationally by Ivy 
      Funds Distributor, Inc., and will be managed by Ivy (its affiliate 
      Waddell & Reed Investment Management Company previously served as 
      subadvisor to the funds). Both Ivy entities are subsidiaries of Waddell 
      & Reed Financial, Inc.
    

      Ivy Funds intends to create a new subsidiary of Ivy Funds Distributor, 
      Inc., to be called Ivy Global Investors, Inc., that will be responsible 
      for the distribution of the UCITS fund range. It also is intended that 
      the SICAV be re-named Ivy Global Investors, with that name attaching to 
      each of the sub-funds within the SICAV (e.g., Ivy Global Investors Asset 
      Strategy Fund).
    

      “This transaction enables us both to serve the non-resident customer 
      market through national broker/dealer firms in the United States and to 
      establish greater international distribution of Ivy’s investment 
      management capabilities,” said Thomas W. Butch, president and CEO of Ivy 
      Funds Distributor, Inc. “It expands our distribution network as well as 
      the range of investors that can access the investment management 
      expertise offered through the Ivy Funds.”
    

      Sub-funds of the SICAV included in the fund adoption transaction are EMG 
      Ivy Asset Strategy Fund and EMG Ivy High Income Fund, which have 
      combined assets under management of approximately $247 million. Three 
      other sub-funds of the SICAV . are under review in Luxembourg: EMG Ivy 
      US Mid Cap Growth Fund, EMG Ivy US Large Cap Growth Fund and EMG Ivy 
      Science and Technology Fund.
    

      As part of the transaction, Ivy Funds expects to hire approximately 
      eight former EMG employees, principally involved in sales and marketing.
    

      Going forward, EMG will partner with Ivy through the distribution of the 
      Ivy products in numerous offshore jurisdictions in Italy, Brazil, and 
      certain Middle Eastern markets, as well as through an EMG SICAV, 
      currently in the process of formation, in the management of a 
      fund-of-funds UCITS that invests in various offshore active funds, 
      including Ivy-managed sub-funds, “smart beta” funds and ETFs.
    

      "We are very pleased to be able to continue to work closely with EMG as 
      they help distribute Ivy products in a number of important global 
      markets and include Ivy in their planned fund-of-funds products," said 
      Butch. "We have worked together effectively, and expect this will 
      continue and even be enhanced as we go forward."
    

      Through its subsidiaries, Waddell & Reed Financial, Inc. (NYSE: WDR) 
      provides investment management and financial planning services to 
      clients throughout the U.S. The firm had approximately $131 billion in 
      total assets under management at March 31, 2014. Ivy Investment 
      Management Company serves as investment advisor to the Ivy Funds, while 
      Ivy Funds Distributor, Inc. serves as principal underwriter and 
      distributor to the Ivy Funds.
    

This release does not constitute or contain an offer, solicitation, 
      recommendation or investment advice with respect to the purchase of the 
      UCITS fund described herein or any security. Prospective investors 
      should carefully consider fund objectives, risks, charges, tax 
      considerations and expenses and other relevant information before 
      investing. For this and more information on the Selector Management Fund 
      SICAV, please request a prospectus and read it carefully before you 
      invest. Prospective investors should also consult their professional 
      advisers as to the suitability of any investment in light of their 
      particular circumstances and applicable citizenship, residence or 
      domicile. Selector Management Fund SICAV has been authorized in 
      Luxembourg as an Undertaking for Collective Investments in Transferable 
      Securities (UCITS). Shares of Selector Management Fund SICAV are only 
      available for certain non-U.S. persons in select transactions outside 
      the United States. The views expressed herein represent the opinions of 
      Ivy Investment Management Co. and are not intended as a forecast or 
      guarantee of future results for any product or service. Investment 
      return and principal value will fluctuate, and it is possible to lose 
      money by investing. Past performance is not a guarantee of future 
      results.



Contacts

      Ivy Media Contact:Roger Hoadley, 913-236-1993VP, Director of 
      CommunicationsorWDR Investor Contact:Nicole Russell, 
      913-236-1880VP, Investor Relations
    













