Company Overview of Ivy Investment Management Company



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Ivy Investment Management Company is a privately owned investment manager. The firm primarily provides its services to investment companies. It also caters to pooled investment vehicles and insurance companies. The firm manages separate client-focused equity, fixed income, and balanced portfolios. It also launches and manages equity, fixed income, and balanced mutual funds. The firm invests in the public equity and fixed income markets across the globe. It also invests in derivatives, commodities, and currency markets. For its equity portion, the firm primarily invests in growth and value stocks of small-cap, mid-cap, and large-cap companies. For its fixed income portion, it invests in high ...
Ivy Investment Management Company is a privately owned investment manager. The firm primarily provides its services to investment companies. It also caters to pooled investment vehicles and insurance companies. The firm manages separate client-focused equity, fixed income, and balanced portfolios. It also launches and manages equity, fixed income, and balanced mutual funds. The firm invests in the public equity and fixed income markets across the globe. It also invests in derivatives, commodities, and currency markets. For its equity portion, the firm primarily invests in growth and value stocks of small-cap, mid-cap, and large-cap companies. For its fixed income portion, it invests in high yield, core, and core intermediate securities. The firm employs a combination of fundamental and quantitative analysis along with both bottom-up and top-down stock picking approach to create its portfolios. It is based in Overland Park, Kansas. Ivy Investment Management Company operates as a subsidiary of Waddell & Reed Financial, Inc.
